The paper discusses hardware acceleration of Deep Neural Networks (DNNs), which is a topic that falls under multiple sub-categories in computer science. The paper specifically focuses on designing a bit-flexible accelerator for DNNs, which involves both computer architecture and machine learning. Therefore, cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also relevant as they deal with neural networks and control systems, respectively. Finally, cs.ET (Embedded Systems) is a possible sub-category as the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed architecture in Verilog and its potential use in embedded systems like Jetson-TX2.
